items.name: AfterSchool
items.description:
Hello everyone.

I decided to finally rename and reupload this model, and clean the gallery as well. This is the same model as before, the only difference is I unbaked the VAE file. My reasoning is maybe someone prefers raw looks. Or you already have this VAE file. Or you wish to attach a different one. The default VAE is the file from schoolmax2.5d, renamed for convenience. Baked VAE version is available as well.

I removed the previous wall of text cause nobody would want to read it. Basically, this model tries to make 2.5d images with painted eyebrows and pubic hair. Sometimes it works, sometimes doesn't. I think it's a decent first step. It can't do hands, it can't do background people (seriously, don't try that), and it's better in portrait mode than in landscape (unless you're doing a landscape, of course), but what's new? It is equally good for SFW and NSFW. Thanks to users lynx and ritcher1, I found this model is extremely sensitive to weights in prompts. So maybe it's not as niche as I thought.

The only drawbacks I found here is that the resulting merge doesn't like positive textual inversions or LORAs. Anything I tried to add, even Master Corneo's POVs, cause it to lose 2.5d effect completely, reverting it into 2d model. What's weird as I never encountered this behavior even on fully photorealistic models. Negative inversions are fine, however.

Now, for settings.

In my tests, DPM++ 2M Karras was the best sampler. Steps from 20 to 32, scale about 10. As of recent, I started to heavily trim my prompts, eliminating useless buzzwords like masterpiece or unity 8k wallpaper from positive part. For negative, I tend to use negative embeddings like bad_prompt_version2, Deep Negative, EasyNegative, and Unspeakable Horrors. on top of basic (worst quality:1.4, low quality:1.4). I increased clip skip to 2 and I like the results. Face restore seems to be not very compatible with this merge, it curses faces. Photo realism tag works extremely well. Eyes are still cursed sometimes, especially when steps are too high. Fingers are almost always cursed, nothing new here. I have xformers enabled so your results may vary a bit, mostly in colors.

Thanks to DiaryOfSta (AniDosMix) and MJXXZ (schoolmax2.5d). Every rights and credits remain by their creators and/or owners. I take no credit beyond the basic mention. Both original authors disabled some kind of commercial use so I'll just disable it altogether. Speak with them, if you have to.

items.name: Divine Koneko Toujou Lora
items.description:
Ive learned a lot making my Naoto lora and applied everything I've learned to remake this lora and I'm very happy with the results. Trained on NAI with 118 images of dxd gacha + some anime screencaps. It's V4 as I've retrained and carefully finetuned it several times until it was perfect. Spent another week on this one, all reviews are very appreciated. Looks good on every model I've tried except animelike, that model just cannibalizes the style and character design. The outfit is pretty consistent but not perfect as the triangle extensions don't always appear. All sample images generated with high res fix.
Tags for main outfit I highly recommend: konekouniform, school uniform, white shirt, skirt, red skirt, black ribbon, black corset, kneehighs, black socks,
Tags for Koneko: Koneko Toujou (DXD), white hair, short hair,

modelVersions.name: Divine_KonekoToujouV4
modelVersions.description:
• Trained on NAI instead of Stable Diffusion 1.5

  • This lora is no longer a generic cat girl and is now consistently recognizable as Koneko and consistent with her body type

  • Main outfit actually works well and is consistent

  • DXD style is now more accurately portrayed

  • Redid all tags in the dataset for more consistency and reduced bleeding which fixed many of the V1 issues with frills/bows/bare shoulders/etc being baked into the model

  • Base activators for main outfit changed to - konekouniform, school uniform, white shirt, skirt,

  • Removed the cat hair ornament from the dataset so it no longer appears

  • Now works perfectly well at 1 weight instead of 0.7 like before

    Parts that are worse:

  • Cat tail may be worse and simply come off screen even when not prompted

  • The style is stronger and may override the checkpoint's style a bit depending on the flexibility of the checkpoint

  • Cat ears and tail may sometimes generate black for some reason

  • Because it's trained on NAI which is trained off Koneko already, it sometimes places card frames/text on some generations even though there isn't any in the dataset

  • Gacha card backgrounds appear more often, but tagging a specific background usually will get rid of them

items.description:
《墨心》—— 昔涓子《琴心》，王孙《巧心》，心哉美矣，故用之焉。

本品由安吉吴仓石、兴化板桥先生、八大山人、山阴伯年等大师之大小写意作品辅以现代人物训练而成。辅以恰当之提示词，诵先贤尊号，襄古今并用之意，明雅俗共举之美。

《疏可走马》—— 字画疏处可以走马，密处不使透风。

这是一个和墨心搭配使用的构图Lora, 一旦使用并再最前前置提示词后，就会采用较大面积留白的构图风格。可以在版本处找到他

注意事项：
1.）CFG范围将会改变风格

  • 1~3 : 大小写意

  • 3~7 : 逐渐工笔

2.）推荐基础模型为ChilloutMix、国风3.2等

3.）《墨心》的推荐Lora权重为0.85以下

4.）《疏可走马》推荐Lora权重为0.7~1

====================================

"MoXin"
Xi Juanzi "Qinxin". Wangsun "QiaoXin", Xin zai mei yi, gu yong zhi yan.

MoXin is a Lora trained from on Chinese painting Masters lived in Ming and Qing dynasties.


“Shukezouma”
Zi hua shu chu ke yi zou ma, mi chu bu shi tou feng.
This is a Lora that major functions in Traditionla Chinese painting composition. Once it is used and preceded by "shukezouma" prompts in the very beginning, it adopts a composition style featuring a large area of negative space.

Tips:

1.) The result style will change within the following CFG ranges:

  • 1~3 : Xieyi Painting

  • 3~7 : Gongbi Painting

2.) It is recommended to use with ChilloutMix, GuoFeng3.2, etc.

3.) It is recommended to use "MoXin"'s Lora weight of 0.85 or lower.

4.) It is recommended to use "Shukezouma"'s Lora weight between 0.7~1

LoRA of Admire Vega (umamusume)

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

Recommend options

  • Trigger words

      • (optional) skirt -> white skirt,

    • Tracen school uniform :

      • tracen school uniform, purple shirt, white skirt, puffy short sleeves, sailor collar, bowtie, pleated skirt, sailor shirt, miniskirt, zettai ryouiki, white thighhighs

    • Casual clothes:

      • pants, long sleeves, blue sweater, turtleneck sweater, ribbed sweater, jeans, jewelry, casual, necklace

      • (optional) object hug, pillow, bed sheet

Use animefull based model

  • Settings

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • If using highres

      • Latent series

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss. Thank you a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned

  • 154 images of fine motion

    • 4x low quality 46 images

    • 8x medium quality 53 images

    • 16x high quality 55 images

    • => 1 epoch = 1488 images

  • replaced character feature tags with admire vega \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, brown hair, purple eyes, etc.

  • using aspect ratio bucketing

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • using dadaptation

  • batch size = 4, 7 epochs trained

  • clip skip = 1

This LoRA may be compatible with animefull-based models (ex. AbyssOrangeMix Series...)

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

Use animefull based model

  • Settings

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use highres.fix to get higher quality image

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • 114 images of mejiro dober

  • replaced character feature tags with mejiro dober \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, brown hair, purple eyes, etc.

  • using aspect ratio bucketing

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • using dadaptation

  • batch size = 4, 7 epochs trained

  • clip skip = 1

items.name: Death Note Lora
items.description:
Just a LORA that emulates the style of the anime Death Note. Strength of 1.0 should work fine for most stuff, but lowering the strength can help if it only throws characters from the show at you. The LORA doesn't like creating people of color without lowering the strength, but is fully capable of doing so.

It does have a hard time reproducing L. I could fix this by manually captioning shots of him from the show, but that's a bit more work than I'm willing to put in. Maybe you'll be able to pull him out with a little creative prompting.

I trained it on around 5,000 still images from the show, so it's quite good at emulating the style. No need to give it a particularly lengthy prompt these images were generated with really simple prompts.

This LORA mixes well with others as well. So if you want a trained character/person in the Death Note style that's possible. If you have any questions, comments, or concerns feel free to send me a message. I'm happy to chat about my methodology.

If you really like it you can buy me a coffee, totally unnecessary, but always welcome. I do this for fun.

items.name: Andrea Botez
items.description:
Andrea Botez is a Canadian chess player and streamer, the younger sister of Alexandra Botez.

Update: Retrained from scratch. I'm having trouble deciding between steps 1200 and 1000. The former seems more consistent, but the latter has produced some great results, so I will probably upload it as version 3.0 later.

Version 3.1 is a 1200-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (4ndr34b0t3z:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

modelVersions.name: v3.0
modelVersions.description: Adding step 1000 as version 3.0 as promised. As I mentioned in the description, I think step 1200 is the superior version because of its consistency, but this one has produced some remarkably good pics, so I think it's worth sharing.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
As with her sister, I've applied my new training method to my dataset of Andrea. The new TI has been trained for 6550 steps and seems less saturated and probably more accurate than the previous version, so I'm uploading it in case you wanna try it. Have fun!

By the way, regarding prompt-building, I suggest you start the prompt with "a photo of", "a picture of", etc., and then you add "4ndreabotez". It seems to be much more precise that way. I've seen results that didn't have much to do with the subject when I started the prompt directly with "4ndreabotez". This is probably a consequence of how I train my models and the prompt template and filewords I use, but it seems unavoidable.
